### Global Variables
@host = http://localhost:8080
@api = /api/auth

### 1. Register a new Tenant and User
POST {{host}}{{api}}/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tenantName": "mycompany",
  "firstName": "Max",
  "lastName": "Mustermann",
  "email": "max@mustermann.de",
  "password": "securePassword123"
}

### 2. Login
# Authenticates and sets 'accessToken' and 'refreshToken' cookies.
# We also capture the tokens into global variables for use in IntelliJ.
POST {{host}}{{api}}/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "max@mustermann.de",
  "password": "securePassword123"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("accessToken", response.body.data.accessToken);
    client.global.set("refreshToken", response.body.data.refreshToken);
%}

### 3. Get Current User Info (Me)
# If cookies are blocked by Secure=true on HTTP, we send it manually here:
GET {{host}}{{api}}/me
Cookie: accessToken={{accessToken}}

### 4. Refresh Access Token
GET {{host}}{{api}}/refresh-token
Cookie: refreshToken={{refreshToken}}

### 5. Logout
POST {{host}}{{api}}/logout
